NAME
    gcloud app regions - view regional availability of App Engine runtime
        environments

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud app regions COMMAND [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    This command can be used to view availability of App Engine standard and
    flexible runtime environments in all geographic regions.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --billing-project,
    --configuration, --flags-file, --flatten, --format, --help,
    --impersonate-service-account, --log-http, --project, --quiet,
    --trace-token, --user-output-enabled, --verbosity.

    Run $ gcloud help for details.

COMMANDS
    COMMAND is one of the following:

     list
        List the availability of flex and standard environments for each
        region.

EXAMPLES
    To view regional availability of App Engine runtime environments, run:

        $ gcloud app regions list

NOTES
    This variant is also available:

        $ gcloud beta app regions

